CCITDevOps :
SCCM - source code condrol (to track only one file 1972)
RCS - revision control system (Track multer file but not directories)
CVSM - Concurrent version control (track multiple files and directories but single user)
SVN - Sub Version (save the information in single server)
     it work on CVCS--Centralized version control system.
GIT - global information tracker (save information in multiple server)
     it work on distrubuted version control system.
GIT Arcitecture/stages :-
             working directory
    git add---      |
              stagging area
                    |     ---git commit
                repository

  working directory-
wd -- where we used to store poject or app related data
staging area -- where developers are used to write a code 
repository -- store our app data in the cloud.


local                                         remote
git                                           github
 git alternative 
how to install git in local system (through unbuntu)
create directory- mkdir git
open directory- cd git
install git or starting git by ** git init
create file- touch index.html
then to add to git ** git add index.html
then we commit on git ** git commit -m "first commit" index.html
then git identity as gmail and name like ** config user.email " user email"
                                         ** config user.name " user name"

then finally ** git commit -m "file name" index.html





